AT 022300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 983 IS CENTRED CLOSE TO THE
ISLE OF WIGHT FLN AND MOV EWARDS INTO THE NEAR CONTINENT BY TUESDAY LUNCHTIME
992. THIS LOW CONTINUING TO DRIFT E AND FILL OVERNIGHT INTO WEDNESDAY LOSING
ITS IDENTITY. PRESSURE WILL BUILD FM THE W AS THE LOW MOVS INTO THE CONTINENT
WITH A GENERALLY SLACK FLOW ACROSS MUCH OF THE CULLERCOATS AREA THROUGH WEDNESDAY.
ON MONDAY EVENING GALES ARE EXP ACROSS FORTIES DOGGER AND FISHER. THESE
WILL CONTINUE OVERNIGHT BEFORE ABATING THROUGH TUESDAY MORNING. STRG WINDS
ARE ALSO EXP FOR A TIME THROUGH VIKING AND FAIR ISLE ON MONDAY EVENING EASING
BY TUESDAY MORNING. WINDS INCR TUESDAY EVENING TO NEAR GALES THROUGH THAMES
DOVER AND WIGHT BUT EASING EARLY ON WEDNESDAY. THEREAFTER NO STRG WINDS ARE
